      "lineNbr": 409,
      "author": {
        "id": 12542
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-02T15:42:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, the SQL script schema being a bit inconsistent as well in that regard :-/\n\nTake a close look at the SQL script schema - it\u0027s got a default charset of latin1 for this table and a explicit UTF8 charset for all fields...\n\nSo this is the \"I wanted to match the SQL script as closely as possible\" thing I mentioned earlier. To later resolve these inconsistencies cleanly with a migration we need to make sure every database out in the field (both the ones fully created by migrations and the ones created by applying the legacy schema) have exactly the same inconsistencies.",
      "parentUuid": "9f6a8fd7_a7727f7b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 409,
        "startChar": 55,
        "endLine": 409,
        "endChar": 73
